## Project Overview

The Personal Nutrition Assistant project aims to empower individuals to make healthier food choices by providing personalized meal recommendations based on their dietary preferences, restrictions, and local grocery availability.

## Project Objectives

### Purpose Statement
The Personal Nutrition Assistant project aims to empower individuals to make healthier food choices by providing personalized meal recommendations based on their dietary preferences, restrictions, and local grocery availability.

### SMART Objectives
1. **Specific & Measurable**
   - Develop MVP mobile/web app within 8 weeks
   - Deliver minimum 3 customized meal suggestions daily per user
   - Achieve user profile creation functionality

2. **Achievable**
   - Integrate one reliable nutrition database API
   - Complete integration by end of Phase 2
   - Ensure accurate nutritional values for all meals

3. **Relevant & Time-Bound**
   - Launch MVP to minimum 20 beta testers within 12 weeks
   - Gather and implement feedback
   - Refine features based on user testing

## Stakeholders and Roles

### Project Team
- Developers
- Designer
- Project Manager
- QA/Testers

### End Users
- Health-conscious individuals seeking personalized nutrition support

### External Stakeholders
- Nutrition database providers
- Potential partners (gyms, dieticians, grocery stores)

### Advisors/Mentors
- Faculty or external stakeholders guiding the project

### Team Responsibilities
- **Project Manager**: Oversees project delivery, timelines, and stakeholder communication
- **Technical Lead**: System architecture, database integration, and backend development
- **UI/UX Designer**: Designs intuitive and user-friendly interfaces
- **Research & Documentation**: Conducts nutritional research, prepares project documentation
- **QA & Testing**: Ensures app functionality, usability, and reliability

## Scope Definition

### In-Scope Features
- User registration and profile creation
- Dietary preferences and restrictions management
- Personalized meal recommendations
- Integration with nutrition API
- Basic grocery list generator

### Out-of-Scope (for MVP)
- Advanced AI-driven coaching features
- Wearable device integrations
- Grocery delivery/e-commerce integration
- Premium features (dietician chat, advanced analytics)

## Risk Management

| Risk | Impact | Likelihood | Mitigation Strategy |
|------|--------|------------|---------------------|
| API Data Unreliability | Incorrect nutrition values | Medium | Choose reliable API with fallback options |
| Scope Creep | Delayed MVP delivery | High | Clearly define MVP features; prioritize essential ones only |
| User Adoption | Low engagement | Medium | Conduct beta testing with targeted users early |
| Team Availability | Workload/absence issues | Low | Distribute responsibilities; maintain backup resources |

## Project Timeline

### Phase 1: Team Setup & Requirements (Week 1-2)
- Finalize roles and collaboration tools
- Gather nutritional data sources
- Establish project infrastructure

### Phase 2: MVP Development (Week 3-6)
- Implement user profiles
- Integrate nutrition API
- Develop basic recommendation engine

### Phase 3: Testing & Refinement (Week 7-9)
- Conduct unit testing
- Perform user testing with beta group
- Refine features based on feedback

### Phase 4: Launch & Feedback (Week 10-12)
- Release MVP to testers
- Collect and implement feedback
- Prepare improvement roadmap
